{"key":"processedPost-11225674","value":{"id":11225674,"first":11212465,"last":11273557,"when":1255275229,"utime":"10/11/09 06:33 PM","content":"Another reason success rates go up so high with a flow hood, is you let it run for an hour or two in a closed room before starting sterile work.&nbsp; During that hour, the flowhood constantly recycles the air, filtering it again and again.&nbsp; The result is very clean air, even if some of it does slip into the sterile flow in front of the flowhood.&nbsp; <br />Using a glovebox properly will give you about a 95% success rate, sometimes higher.&nbsp; Using a flowhood properly will give a 99.99% success rate, and you have more room to work.<br />RR","title":"Re: question regarding laminar flow"}}